# Context Discovery & Awareness

## Core Behavior
At the start of each new chat, or when the conversation shifts to a new feature or part of the code, you must proactively gather context before making assumptions or writing code.

## Actions to Take
* **Scan Docs:** Search for and read any relevant `.md`, `.mdx`, or `docs/` files related to the current topic.
* **Scan Docstrings:** Look up and read important module-level documentation, function docstrings, and type definitions that you deem relevant.
* **Follow the Code:** If a lifecycle or mechanism relies on internal libraries or downstream functions, use your search tools to find and read their specific docstrings, even if they are not in the immediate vicinity.

## Philosophy
Do not guess how local systems or complex lifecycles work. Always look for the written truth in project documentation and code comments first.
